@node 08024.013
Subject: StormMesa, VBCC and StormC
From: AHippauf@t-online.de (Andreas Hippauf)
Date: Tue, 21 Dec 1999 09:10:51 +0100

Hi,

like I promised, I put a short mail in here, when I solve my problem!
Did you remember? I could with some help of Sam Jordan, compile our
lightforce-source (mesa-based 3D-game) with stormC.
But when running the compiled programm, only textoutput was shown, no
3D-graphics at all! Mesa-Stats reported, that 3D-graphics was drawn
using hardware-acceleration and with vbcc instead of stormc the programm
showed the 3D-graphics without any complaints!
Strange? What was the bug?
*gluLookAt();*

The last 3 numbers, which give the upvector, where set to zero and
wether vbcc nore stormc did complain about that. vbcc even worked fine
with this setting. After correcting gluLookAt() and setting last number
(z) to 1, it now shows 3D-graphics with stormc as well as with vbcc!

Great!

So I once again, state, that there is no problem with stormc, stormmesa
or warp3d. It was simply my fault. A bug and this one was really hard to
find, as one compiler did not care about it!

Greetings to all and merry christmas in advance!

 Andreas Hippauf

